description: Numbers that are the sum of two (possibly negative) cubes in at least 2 ways.
links: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
mathematica: ok[n_] := If[Length[PowersRepresentations[n, 2, 3]] >= 2, True, r = Reduce[n == x^3 + y^3, {x, y}, Integers]; If[r === False, False, Length[Union[Sort /@ ({x, y} /. {ToRules[r]})]] >= 2]]; Select[Range[13860], If[ok[#], Print[#]; True, False] &] (* _Jean-FranÃ§ois Alcover_, Apr 11 2011 *)
